                        "Description": {
                            "HorizontalTextAlignment": "Center",
                            "Lines": [
                                "I used to use a third-party website builder for my portfolio website, but with time, \nI noticed that the <*amount of control*> I had on the design was not ideal.",
                                "So, I got to work and built this new version of my portfolio website, using a new, interesting technology: <*Blazor*>."
                            ]
                        }
                    },
                    "Sections": [
                        {
                            "MainContent": {
                                "Excerpt": {
                                    "Title": "What is Blazor?",
                                    "Description": {
                                        "HorizontalTextAlignment": "Left",
                                        "Lines": [
                                            "Blazor is a new way to develop web applications, based on the already existing .NET ecosystem. It can run either on a web server (<*Blazor Server*>)or on the client, via web-assembly (<*Blazor Web Assembly*>).",
                                            "One of the greatest features of this tool is that one can build a rich web application with <*minimal to no JavaScript*>: almost all (<*if not all!*>) logic can be done with <*C#*>.",
                                            "And with this incredible technology, I was able to bring this website to <*life*>."
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    "Links": []
                                }
                            },
